HEADWORD: Hydrostatics
<hw>Hy`dro*stat"ics</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>hydrostatique</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>The branch of
science which relates to the pressure and equilibrium of nonelastic
fluids, as water, mercury, etc.; the principles of statics applied to
water and other liquids.</def>⟦br⟧
